<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-029-642  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 029 642.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Jan 10 1990 n1339* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>HTEC has Pioneer's combined erasable- write-once optical drive forthe UK.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   HTEC Ltd. (distribution).andO;Product:   Pioneer DEC-500 (WORM drive) (distribution).andO;Topic:     DistributorsWORMOptical DisksDisk Drives.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>HTEC HAS PIONEER'S COMBINED ERASABLE- WRITE-ONCE OPTICALandM;DRIVE FOR THE UKandM;A new optical disk drive from Pioneer that can be used for both rewritable,and write once read many disks, is being distributed in the UK by HTEC Ltd ofSouthampton.andP;  Launched at the Tokyo Data Show in October, (CI No 1,289),DEC-500 facilitates both long and short term storage by matching the designof the rewritable disk to the servo format used in the write-once-read-manyoptical disk system.andP;  The drive can write data to and read data from bothtypes, either under manual or automatic control.andP;  Average seek time for thewrite-once-read-many system is 53mS, and data transfer is 1.5Mbytes-per-second.andP;  The drive is manufactured by Pioneer in Tokyo, and comeswith a SCSI interface as the DE-V5000, or as a subsystem version with its ownpower supply, the DE-S5000.andP;  HTEC's data storage business was acquired for anundisclosed sum from Legend Group in February last year (CI No 1,120).andO;</TEXT></DOC>